    "body": "<!-- Thank you for your contribution! We appreciate it. The following guidelines will help improve your pull request and facilitate feedback. If anything is unclear, don't hesitate to submit your pull request and ask the maintainers for assistance. -->\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nSee #4654 #4655 \r\nMooncake transfer engine is a high-performance, zero-copy data transfer library. To achieve efficient PD disaggregation, mooncake team wants to adopt mooncake transfer engine as the transport layer.\r\n\r\n### Usage\r\nKnow how to install mooncake transfer engine [here](https://github.com/kvcache-ai/Mooncake/blob/main/doc/en/build.md). We provide a new [adaptor](https://github.com/kvcache-ai/Mooncake/commit/db5929edd128e9df787e664236bc71446adcdc02) and new [interface](https://github.com/kvcache-ai/Mooncake/commit/fec09ff52d22c8e647bd90e13a0ac69acc9208e2) for using transfer engine in SGLang. Note that current implementation is just a prototype.\r\n\r\nSGLang PD disaggregation: https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/pull/4880#issuecomment-2775457846\r\n\r\n### Known Limitations:\r\n\r\n1. Failure handling is currently missing.\r\n2. We assume each server only has one SGLang instance, which means it doesn't support multiple P/D instances located on one server at the same time.\r\n3. If GDR is not supported, it should fall back to double buffering for data copies (we don't implement it now).\r\n4. The current implementation relies on ETCD for coordination. We plan to replace this with implementing the bootstrap server in conn.py.\r\n\r\nCC: @james0zan @ShangmingCai @XucSh @alogfans @ByronHsu @zhyncs \r\n\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\n\r\n### Workflow:\r\n1. KVManager init MooncakeTransferEngine\r\n    1. Registering all GPU addresses into RDMA via KVArgs\r\n    2. Initialize a map (request_pool: RequestPoolType) from bootstrap_room to metadata (kv_indices/aux_token)\r\n    3. Add a zmq server bound to a specific port. For KVSender/Receiver, there is a dedicated thread for polling messages from KVSender.\r\n2. KVSender kvsend: \r\n    1. Add [bootstrap_room: [kv_indices, aux_token]] to request_pool.\r\n3. KVReceiver init: Add [bootstrap_room: [kv_indices, aux_token]] to request_pool. Send metadata (bootstrap_room, kv_data_ptrs, aux_data_ptrs...) to KVSender via zmq, as a Start for KVSender prefill thread\r\n4. KVSender prefill thread\r\n    1. Recv metadata from KVReceiver (bootstrap_room, kv_data_ptrs, aux_data_ptrs...) via zmq\r\n    2. Perform GDR-based RDMA Write using mooncake transferSync\r\n    3. Send the bootstrap_room and Done signal to KVReceiver\r\n5. KVReceiver decode thread\r\n    1. Recv bootstrap_room from KVSender\r\n    2. Pop above bootstrap_room in request_pool\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n\r\n- [ ] Format your code according to the [Code Formatting with Pre-Commit](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#code-formatting-with-pre-commit).\r\n- [ ] Add unit tests as outlined in the [Running Unit Tests](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#running-unit-tests-adding-to-ci).\r\n- [ ] Update documentation / docstrings / example tutorials as needed, according to [Writing Documentation](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#writing-documentation-running-docs-ci).\r\n- [ ] Provide throughput / latency benchmark results and accuracy evaluation results as needed, according to [Benchmark and Profiling](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/benchmark_and_profiling.html) and [Accuracy Results](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/accuracy_evaluation.html).\r\n- [ ] For reviewers: If you haven't made any contributions to this PR and are only assisting with merging the main branch, please remove yourself as a co-author when merging the PR.\r\n- [ ] Please feel free to join our Slack channel at https://slack.sglang.ai to discuss your PR.\r\n",
